 "conclusion": "Closed-loop observational data cannot identify the insulin sensitivity here. The homeostasis the loop enforces creates two killers: (1) glucose reverts toward target regardless of insulin (~46 mg/dL drop from BG 160 with zero insulin), and that reversion is collinear with IOB (corr 0.56, the loop doses by glucose), so the insulin term collapses when reversion is controlled; (2) at target the loop holds BG there, so almost no excursion exists to measure (few near-target 4h windows, and those that exist read a loop-suppressed value). The best per-user ISF at 100 therefore comes from tuned profiles or the cross-sectional K/\u221aTDD cold-start, not from drop/IOB."
